# Documentation rule

Docs are project memory.

Use these roles:

- `README.md`: public entry point.
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`: durable architecture.
- `PLAN.md`: current phase and next work.
- `AGENTS.md`: compact AI agent context.
- `docs/PROJECT_STRATEGY.md`: product strategy.
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT_STRATEGY.md`: engineering strategy.
- `docs/ROADMAP.md`: completed and future phases.
- `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md`: retained backlog.
- `docs/AI_COENGINEERING.md`: ChatGPT and Cursor workflow.
- specs: contracts and invariants.
- historical docs: completed execution criteria.

When moving or renaming docs, update links.

When a feature is deferred, preserve it in `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md` if it remains desirable.

Mark historical execution docs clearly rather than letting them look like active plans.

When a **planning-only** vertical closes (e.g. Slice 2 queue **D** weather/cloud participation spec in `docs/specs/scene/weather-cloud-composition-plan.md`), sync `PLAN.md` closed increment, `docs/ROADMAP.md`, `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md` (pointer if durable), `docs/AI_COENGINEERING.md`, and `README.md` scheduling bullets so “planning vs implementation” stays obvious. When **Slice 2 queues B/C** close (composition baseline complete—eight intrinsics + third twilight; no standing ninth+ intrinsic or fourth+ twilight default PRs), move **default next PR** language to **Phase 8 / queue A** (sourced substrate or explicit scope) in the handoff table and state that **B**/**C** reopen only with **explicit product scope**. When queue **A (2)** substrates close (land cover, bathymetry, climate normals, population density **`equirect-world-population-gpw-v1`**), keep **default next** on queue **A** until a new sourced family or explicit polish appears—not on composition filler PRs.

When a shipped vertical slice changes product behavior (e.g. overlay readability presentation or **new / renamed `scene.overlayReadability.perLayer` keys** beyond the six shipped defaults — `grid`, `solarAnalemma`, `subsolarMarker`, `sublunarMarker`, `cityPins`, `staticEquirectOverlay` per [`src/config/v2/sceneConfig.ts`](src/config/v2/sceneConfig.ts); or **new / renamed base-map `capabilities`** that affect upstream overlay lift (the shipped intrinsic set is `reliefShaded`, `boundaryDense`, `chromaticDense`, `bathymetryShaded`, `fineScaleTexture`, `labelDense`, `etchedReliefDense`, `sunGlintDense`, plus `overlayOptimized` / `darkFriendly` multipliers—sync when extended); or **new durable base-map family ids** in `src/assets/maps/base-map-catalog.json` that change user-visible inventory or provenance claims (even when reusing existing capability keys—sync `README.md`, `PLAN.md` / `docs/ROADMAP.md` Phase 5–8, and `docs/maps/*`; when onboarding static equirect rasters from 0…360° sources, document **dateline roll** to −180…+180° in `docs/maps/MAP_ASSET_SOURCES.md` and add or update asset registration tests such as `bathymetryOnboardedAsset.test.ts`, `landcoverOnboardedAsset.test.ts`, or `climateNormalsOnboardedAsset.test.ts`, or `populationOnboardedAsset.test.ts` when product-critical); or **new / changed base-map selector attribution fields** (`attribution`, `licenseNote`, `sourceLinks` on catalog entries—sync selector UX claims and `PLAN.md` queue **A** when the default next vertical moves); or **month-aware selector UX** (catalog copy for `monthOfYear` families, active UTC civil month indication in `BaseMapStyleControl`, `variantMode` on `BaseMapOption`—sync `PLAN.md` handoff queue **A** when the default next vertical moves); or **clearing `transitionalPlaceholder` / provenance-only updates** for an **existing** base-map id when inventory truth changes (e.g. **`equirect-world-geology-v1`** ship raster + preview, **`equirect-world-bathymetry-etopo-v1`** ship raster + preview + registration test, **`equirect-world-landcover-modis-v1`** ship raster + preview + registration test, **`equirect-world-topography-ne-v1`** bundled `previewThumbnailSrc` + thumb, or **`equirect-world-legacy-v1`** bundled `previewThumbnailSrc` + `world-equirectangular-thumb.jpg`—sync `docs/maps/*`, `PLAN.md` handoff, and `AGENTS.md`; when queue **A (2)** closes, update **default next** to **Slice 2 / queue B** unless a new sourced substrate re-opens queue **A**); or **meaningful upstream planetary illumination / twilight sampling changes** (including cumulative constants-only tuning passes in `illuminationShading.ts`, e.g. **second** and **third** narrow atmospheric passes doc-finalized in `PLAN.md` / `docs/ROADMAP.md`)) documented as a phase in `PLAN.md`), sync `README.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md` maturity, `PLAN.md`, `docs/ROADMAP.md`, `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md`, `docs/PROJECT_STRATEGY.md`, `docs/AI_COENGINEERING.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `docs/DEVELOPMENT_STRATEGY.md`, `docs/maps/MAP_ASSET_SOURCES.md`, `docs/maps/MAP_ASSET_STRATEGY.md`, and `.cursor/rules/050-docs-and-roadmap.mdc` so “shipped vs future” stays obvious without reading source.
